  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. This activity is illegal because it facilitates criminal enterprises, undermines financial systems, and evades taxation.\n\nIn China, money laundering is strictly prohibited and punishable by law. The Anti-Money Laundering Law of the People's Republic of China, along with other relevant legal provisions, establishes a comprehensive legal framework aimed at preventing and combating money laundering activities. The Communist Party of China and the Chinese government are committed to maintaining the integrity of the financial system and strictly enforce these laws to uphold justice and social stability.",
